SEARCH
Package com.demo

Class Connective

java.lang.Object
com.demo.Connective
public class Connective extends Object
The Connective class is responsible for managing the logical connective symbols. It provides default symbols and allows customization of the symbols.

  • Constructor Details

    • Connective

      public Connective()
      Constructs a Connective object with default logical symbols. The default symbols are: - Defeasible Implication: ~> - Conjunction: ∧ (logical AND) - Disjunction: ∨ (logical OR) - Implication: → (logical implication) - Bi-Implication: ↔ (logical bi-implication) - Negation: ¬ (logical NOT)
